Package: xenofetch
Version: 1.0.0
Section: utils
Priority: optional
Architecture: all
Depends: bash (>= 4.0), coreutils, grep, gawk | mawk, sed, procps
Recommends: lm-sensors, pciutils, net-tools, curl, hostname
Suggests: lspci, xrandr
Maintainer: Anton Schmidt <cptcr@proton.me>
Description: Enhanced system information display tool
 Xenofetch is a powerful command-line system information tool that displays
 detailed hardware and software information in beautifully styled tables.
 It provides comprehensive system diagnostics including CPU, memory, storage,
 network, and process information with colorful output.
 .
 Features:
  * Beautiful colored output with gradient effects
  * Comprehensive system information display
  * Cross-platform compatibility
  * Lightweight and fast
  * Customizable styling options
  * Real-time system monitoring
  * Network diagnostics
  * Temperature monitoring (requires lm-sensors)
  * Process analysis
Homepage: https://github.com/cptcr/xenofetch
Vcs-Git: https://github.com/cptcr/xenofetch.git
Vcs-Browser: https://github.com/cptcr/xenofetch